     An operation ID to use for the *path operation*.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = None,\n    response_model_include: Annotated[\n        Optional[Set[str]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        A set of attribute names to include in the response.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = None,\n    response_model_exclude: Annotated[\n        Optional[Set[str]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        A set of attribute names to exclude from the response.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = None,\n    response_model_by_alias: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        Whether to use field aliases in the response model.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = True,\n    response_model_exclude_unset: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        Whether to exclude fields that are not set in the response.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = False,\n    response_model_exclude_defaults: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        Whether to exclude fields that have default values in the response.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = False,\n    response_model_exclude_none: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        Whether to exclude fields that are None in the response.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = False,\n    include_in_schema: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        Whether to include the *path operation* in the schema.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = True,\n    response_class: Annotated[\n        Optional[Type[Response]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        The response class to use for the operation.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = None,\n    name: Annotated[\n        Optional[str],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        A name for the *path operation*.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = None,\n    callbacks: Annotated[\n        Optional[List[BaseRoute]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        A list of callbacks to be applied to the *path operation*.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = None,\n    openapi_extra: Annotated[\n        Optional[Dict[str, Any]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        Extra OpenAPI fields to be added to the *path operation*.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = None,\n    generate_unique_id_function: Annotated[\n        Optional[Callable[[APIRoute], str]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n        A function to generate unique IDs for the *path operation*.\n        \"\"\")\n    ] = None,\n) -> Callable[[DecoratedCallable], DecoratedCallable]:\n    ...\n```\n\n### 主要职责\n`put` 方法的主要职责是：\n1. **注册一个 HTTP PUT 路径操作**：将传入的路径（`path`）与一个 HTTP PUT 方法绑定。\n2. **返回一个装饰器**：该装饰器用于装饰一个函数（即路径操作函数），并将该函数注册到 FastAPI 应用的路由表中。\n3. **支持丰富的配置选项**：通过参数（如 `response_model`、`status_code`、`tags`、`dependencies` 等）来定制 OpenAPI 文档、请求验证、响应模型等行为。\n4. **内部调用 `api_route` 方法**：`put` 方法最终会调用 `self.api_route(path, methods=[\"PUT\"], ...)` 来完成实际的路由注册。\n\n### 函数调用链\n1. `FastAPI.put()` 被调用。\n2. 内部调用 `self.api_route(path, methods=[\"PUT\"], ...)`。\n3. `api_route` 方法创建一个 `APIRoute` 实例，并将其添加到应用的路由列表中。\n4. 返回一个装饰器，该装饰器在装饰函数时，将函数与路由绑定。\n\n### 总结\n- **类**: `FastAPI`\n- **文件**: `fastapi/applications.py`\n- **行号**: 约 400 行（具体版本可能不同）\n- **参数**: 包含 `path` 和大量可选参数（如 `response_model`、`status_code`、`tags` 等）\n- **职责**: 注册 HTTP PUT 路径操作，返回装饰器，支持 OpenAPI 文档和请求/响应处理。",
