      "model_answer": "根据提供的源码片段和 FastAPI 的常见实现，`patch` 是 `FastAPI` 类的一个方法，用于注册处理 HTTP PATCH 请求的路由操作。\n\n### 文件名与行号\n- **文件名**: `fastapi/applications.py`\n- **行号**: 通常在 `patch` 方法定义处，具体行号可能因版本略有不同，但一般在 `get`、`post` 等方法附近。例如，在 FastAPI 0.95.0 版本中，`patch` 方法定义在第 300 行左右。\n\n### 参数列表\n`patch` 方法的参数列表通常如下（基于常见 FastAPI 源码）：\n```python\ndef patch(\n    self,\n    path: Annotated[\n        str,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            The path for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ],\n    *,\n    response_model: Annotated[\n        Any,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            The response model for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    status_code: Annotated[\n        Optional[int],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            The status code for the response.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    tags: Annotated[\n        Optional[List[str]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Tags for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    dependencies: Annotated[\n        Optional[Sequence[Depends]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Dependencies for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    summary: Annotated[\n        Optional[str],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Summary for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    description: Annotated[\n        Optional[str],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Description for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    response_description: Annotated[\n        str,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Description for the response.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = \"Successful Response\",\n    responses: Annotated[\n        Optional[Dict[Union[int, str], Dict[str, Any]]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Additional responses for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    deprecated: Annotated[\n        Optional[bool],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Whether the operation is deprecated.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    operation_id: Annotated[\n        Optional[str],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Unique identifier for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    response_model_include: Annotated[\n        Optional[Set[str]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Fields to include in the response model.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    response_model_exclude: Annotated[\n        Optional[Set[str]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Fields to exclude from the response model.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    response_model_by_alias: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Whether to use aliases in the response model.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = True,\n    response_model_exclude_unset: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Whether to exclude unset fields from the response model.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = False,\n    response_model_exclude_defaults: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Whether to exclude default fields from the response model.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = False,\n    response_model_exclude_none: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Whether to exclude None fields from the response model.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = False,\n    include_in_schema: Annotated[\n        bool,\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Whether to include the operation in the OpenAPI schema.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = True,\n    response_class: Annotated[\n        Type[Response],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            The response class to use.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = Default(JSONResponse),\n    name: Annotated[\n        Optional[str],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Name for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    callbacks: Annotated[\n        Optional[List[BaseRoute]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Callbacks for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    openapi_extra: Annotated[\n        Optional[Dict[str, Any]],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Extra OpenAPI fields for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = None,\n    generate_unique_id_function: Annotated[\n        Callable[[\"APIRoute\"], str],\n        Doc(\"\"\"\n            Function to generate unique IDs for the operation.\n            ...\n        \"\"\"),\n    ] = Default(generate_unique_id),\n) -> Callable[[DecoratedCallable], DecoratedCallable]:\n    ...\n```\n\n### 主要职责\n`patch` 方法的主要职责是：\n1. **注册路由**：将指定的路径（`path`）与一个 HTTP PATCH 方法绑定，用于处理部分更新资源的请求。\n2. **装饰器功能**：返回一个装饰器，该装饰器可以将一个函数（通常是异步或同步的端点处理函数）注册为 FastAPI 应用的路由处理函数。\n3. **参数传递**：接收并传递各种配置参数（如 `response_model`、`status_code`、`tags`、`dependencies` 等），这些参数会影响 OpenAPI 文档生成、请求验证、响应处理等行为。\n4. **内部调用**：通常内部会调用 `self.add_api_route` 方法，将路径、HTTP 方法（`\"PATCH\"`）以及所有配置参数传递给路由注册逻辑。\n\n### 函数调用链\n1. `FastAPI.patch()` 被调用时，会解析传入的参数。\n2. 内部调用 `self.add_api_route(path, endpoint, methods=[\"PATCH\"], ...)`，其中 `endpoint` 是被装饰的函数。\n3. `add_api_route` 方法（定义在 `fastapi/applications.py` 或 `fastapi/routing.py`）会创建一个 `APIRoute` 实例，并将其添加到应用的路由表中。\n4. 最终，当收到匹配的 HTTP PATCH 请求时，FastAPI 会通过路由表找到对应的 `APIRoute`，并执行其处理函数。\n\n### 注意事项\n- 具体行号和参数细节可能因 FastAPI 版本不同而略有差异，建议查阅对应版本的源码。\n- 参数中的 `Annotated` 类型提示用于文档生成，实际运行时不影响逻辑。",
